Its probably worth noting here that DPT made the mistake of using license
trapped include files from the I2O sig. Everything I understand is that it
is there wish that the code could be in the kernel. You do get full source
to their DPT specific I2O driver too.
> Without starting a holy war, the AMI cards perfom just as well and have drivers
> that are included in the kernel. 
And ICP Vortex have been supported with all the utils on Linux too for a long
time etc. There is plenty of choice
